frameDefinitions: This is an abstract frame for durative activities, in which the Agent enters an ongoing state of the Activity, remains in this state for some Duration of Time, and leaves this state either by finishing or by stopping.
A Supply of a Resource is kept safe and available for a future Use.
A trial is a process conducted in a Court before a Judge and (usually) a Jury in which the participants meet in order to decide a Case.
An Agent attempts to achieve a Goal using some Means.
An Arguer presents a Content, along with Support, to an Addressee.
frameExamples: Our <t>supply</t> of food is running low.
John <t>tried</t> using a crowbar to open the door.
Jan <t>argued</t> that the evidence was inadmissable.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the <fen>Activity</fen> in which the  <fen>Agent</fen>  is engaged.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is engaged in the <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Activity</fen> occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Activity</fen> occurs.
This role denotes the <fen>Supply</fen> of <fen>Resource</fen>s. It is incorporated into each LU in this frame.
The goods or commodity that is being stored in a <fen>Supply</fen>.
The future <fen>Use</fen> for the <fen>Resource</fen>.
The entity that possesses the <fen>Supply</fen>.
The legal label for the crime that the <fen>Defendant</fen> is accused of.
The specific room where the participants in a Trial meet.

The individual or group which is responsible for promoting the welfare of the  <fen>Defendant</fen> during a Trial, usually involving the contention that the <fen>Defendant</fen> is innocent of the <fen>Charges</fen>.
The group of individuals who observe the Trial and ultimately attempt to come to a verdict.
The individual or group responsible for promoting the interests of the state in the Trial, prototypically including presenting arguments for the guilt of the <fen>Defendant</fen>.
The person charged with an offence.
The official who directs and presides over the Trial.
The <fen>Case</fen> which a Trial is convened to decide.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the trial occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the trial occurs.
The <fen>Agent</fen> makes an attempt to achieve a <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is what the <fen>Agent</fen> attempts to achieve.
This role identifies the <fen>Means</fen> by which an attempt occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the attempt occurs.
The place where an attempt is made.

The <fen>Arguer</fen> wants the <fen>Addressee</fen> to entertain the <fen>Content</fen>, which can be a proposition to be believed or a course of action to be taken, based on the <fen>Support</fen> presented.
The <fen>Arguer</fen> presents the <fen>Content</fen> before the <fen>Addressee</fen>.
The Time at which an <fen>Arguer</fen> makes an argument for the <fen>Content</fen>.
This role identifies the location where an argument is made by an <fen>Arguer</fen>.
listRoleExamples: India has made great strides in agriculture and now not only meets it own grain needs but has a sizeable reserve <fex>of basic grains, mainly rice and wheat</fex>.
Due to restrictions imposed by our export control, the Japanese have begun to use a portion of their <fex>war</fex> reserve of petroleum.
In 1997, <fex>France's</fex> stock of unirradiated civil plutonium increased to 72 tons.
John tried using a crowbar <fex>to enter the locked door</fex>.
<fex>On the bridge</fex> he tried the crowbar.
Jan argued <fex>that the evidence was inadmissable</fex>.
<fex>Jan</fex> argued that the evidence was inadmissable.
The government argued <fex>in August</fex> that the prisoners should not be released
The young men will be arguing their policies <fex>in the school auditorium</fex>.
